{
  "text": "Just wondering if the transparency of the garment in the third card indicates the semi-permeability nature of the veil between conscious and subconscious. I am Ra. This is a thoughtful perception and it cannot be said to be incorrect. However, the intended suggestion in a general is an echo of our earlier suggestion that the nature of a catalyst is that of the unconscious. That is outward catalyst comes through the veil. All that you perceive seems to be consciously perceived. This is not the correct supposition. All that you perceive is perceived as catalyst unconsciously, by the shall we say time that the mind begins its appreciation of catalyst. That catalyst has been filtered through the veil, and in some cases, much is veiled in the most apparently clear perception.",
